#4550
@@gThe Boundary Pillar Road@@N~
@@gThe woodland releases you here without ceremony â the canopy breaks and the
sky opens in a long southward sweep. A carved granite pillar stands at the
road's edge, its north face lettered in Midgaard standard script and its south
face carved with a single word: Rakuen.@@N @@WAdvisory boards flanking the
pillar carry weather-sign instructions, flood-season detour maps, and a freshly
stenciled notice about registration requirements at the Lower Dispatch House
to the south.@@N @@bThe road ahead is packed earth over old flagstone, worn
into a comfortable depression by generations of southbound feet. A second
smaller board, hand-lettered and nailed below the official notices, reads:
'queue behavior observed and recorded'.@@N
