#4551
@@gSplit-Path at the Redwater Braid@@N~
@@gThe road forks here at a wide stand of flood-scarred alder, the trunk bark
stained the pale red that gives the Redwater its name. @@gThe western fork
curves toward an elevated overlook above the flood channel; the main road
continues south toward the Dispatch House.@@N @@WA route-board cluster stands
at the fork, its posts carrying six separate notices â three official, one
citizen-posted complaint about notice proliferation, one response to that
complaint, and one advisory telling travelers to disregard the last two.@@N
@@bA broken wagon spoke has been wedged into the fork post as an informal
depth marker for the adjacent braid channel; the current water level sits
well below the warning notch.@@N
