@@gSouthward Guide-Post Run@@N~
@@gThe approach narrows between two rows of carved guide-posts, each bearing
distance tallies to the Lower Dispatch House, to the Central Market, and to
the Bloom Pavilion. @@gSome posts carry additional unofficial markings â route
amendments, seasonal warnings, and at least one carving that appears to be a
satirical caricature of a Bloom Council steward.@@N @@bThe ground here is
firm but shows the scalloped ridges of seasonal flooding along the verge; the
road builders laid a raised crown on the road bed to keep the center dry.@@N
@@WA fresh amendment placard has been hammered over an older one on the
easternmost post, partially covering a warning about the eastern flood drum
platform.@@N
