#4553
@@cRedwater Flood Overlook@@N~
@@cA broad step of natural bedrock projects above the flood channel here,
worn smooth by the boots of generations of flood-watchers. @@cThe Redwater
channel is visible below â presently low and clear, running over sand and
pebble in long translucent sheets.@@N @@bHigh-water marks are carved into the
rock face at irregular intervals, some dating back to the early settlement
years by the style of the numerals. @@bThe highest mark sits considerably
above the current level, a reminder that the flood-routing works in the lower
terraces were not built for comfort.@@N @@gThe main southward road is visible
from the overlook to the west, and the flood drum platform can be reached by
descending the far side of the rock step to the south.@@N
