@@cFlood Warning Drum Platform@@N~
@@cA raised timber platform supports four barrel drums, each painted with
flood-season color codes and positioned to be audible across the lower
approach. @@cThe drums show the scars of regular use â the heads have been
replaced at least twice, and the mallets hanging from the frame posts are
worn smooth at the grip.@@N @@bThe platform attendant's log is tacked to the
south post under a rain cover; the most recent entries note 'channel stable,
no advisory' for seventeen consecutive days.@@N @@WA large civic notice
affixed to the north post describes the drum signal codes in numbered order,
with a footnote that the codes were amended during the Ash-and-Iron period and
the pre-amendment codes should be disregarded.@@N
