older than the current structure by at least a century â the lintel stone
carries a founding-era carving of a compass rose that has been partially
obscured by later civic seal stamps.@@N @@bThe floor just inside the arch is
worn to a concave polish by foot traffic; a shallow scraper bar is set into
the threshold for mud removal, though the bar itself is clogged with dried mud.@@N
