@@WTerrace Junction@@N~
@@WThe terrace junction is the first true decision point inside Rakuen proper.
@@WThree ways diverge here: east toward the Causeway Quarter along the main
civic spine, south into the Lower Terraces along the flood-prone residential
descent, and west back to the stair landing and the approach road.@@N
@@bA standing stone at the center of the junction is a Promise Stone â one of
the founding-era granite markers carved with the Compact's core pledges. @@bThis
one carries the third pledge, concerning rotating stewardship, partially
obscured by a bracket-mounted civic notice about current ration allocation
procedures.@@N @@WSmall knots of travelers typically pause here, adjusting
packs and consulting the route-boards before splitting toward their separate
destinations.@@N
