@@GBloom Pavilion â Main Hall@@N~
@@GThe Bloom Pavilion is Rakuen's oldest civic structure, built in Year Seven
on a foundation of river-gathered stone and roofed with a living canopy of
trained ivy and flowering creepers. @@GThe ivy is a different cultivar than
the original â maintained through three rebuilds and the careful preservation
of root cuttings â but the living roof has never been interrupted, a fact
the Bloom Council describes as proof that the founding ideal persists.@@N
@@bThe main hall is open-sided in the traditional manner, its columns carved
with the founding compact's five principles in rotating repeat. @@bStewardship
rotation announcements, festival ceremonies, and circle mediations all take
place on this floor, which has been polished by generations of civic shoes.@@N
@@WA carved lectern at the hall's center carries the standard Compact text,
and a framed portrait of Verath Solen hangs on the north pillar â the
idealist frozen in civically convenient perpetuity.@@N
