residences, its walls hung with placard tributes to former stewards
who served full rotation terms. @@bThe placard system was established
as a way of honoring civic service without creating permanent offices;
the placards rotate off the wall after three generations and are
archived.@@N @@bSome placards are more recent than others; a cluster
near the east end commemorates stewards from the Ash-and-Iron period
and several of them carry supplementary notes describing how the
honored steward's term ended under emergency protocols.@@N
